<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-05-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="732" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2709</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Commissioner in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-05-24"><hi rend="italic">May 24,
                                1923</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch
                            No. 52 of April 30, last, and views with satisfaction your endeavor to
                            make clear in the Dominican Republic the neutral position of the
                            American Government and of yourself in the presidential contest.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William
                                    Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>